empted=yes }}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Prominent members==\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT MAKE ADDITIONS TO THIS LIST WHICH DO NOT HAVE APPROPRIATE REFERENCES-->\n\n* [[Nitish Kumar]], President of Janata Dal (United) & [[List of Chief Ministers of Bihar|Chief Minister of Bihar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/bihar-chief-minister-nitish-kumar-is-new-jdu-chief/article8458031.ece|title=Nitish Kumar is new JD(U) chief|newspaper=The Hindu|date=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Harivansh Narayan Singh]] \u2013 [[Deputy Chairman of the Rajya Sabha]] (2018)\n* [[K.C. Tyagi]], Secretary General & National Spokesperson.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.janatadalunited.org/secretary_general.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100923021419/http://www.janatadalunited.org/secretary_general.html|url-status = dead|archive-date=23 September 2010|title=The Secretary General|date=23 September 2010|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://164.100.47.5/webcom/typewise.aspx?type=DRSCRS |title=Rajya Sabha: Department Related Parliamentary Standing Committees |publisher=164.100.47.5 |accessdate=12 March 2017 |url-status = live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20170312020752/http://164.100.47.5/webcom/typewise.aspx?type=DRSCRS |archivedate=12 March 2017  }}</ref>\n* [[Vijay Kumar Chaudhary]], Speaker of [[Bihar Legislative Assembly]], Former Bihar [[JD(U)]] President, Former Leader of [[JD(U)]] Legislature Party, .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/nitish-confidante-vijay-chaudhary-is-new-bihar-speaker/1/536704.html|url-status = live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406110247/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/nitish-confidante-vijay-chaudhary-is-new-bihar-speaker/1/536704.html|archivedate=6 April 2017|title=Nitish confidante Vijay Chaudhary is new Bihar Speaker}}</ref>\n* [[Ramchandra Prasad Singh]], National general secretary (Organization), Party leader in Rajya Sabha.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/bihar-polls-meet-the-backroom-boys-in-the-battle-for-bihar/20150922.htm|url-status = live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406021442/http://www.rediff.com/news/report/bihar-polls-meet-the-backroom-boys-in-the-battle-for-bihar/20150922.htm|archivedate=6 April 2017|title=Meet the backroom boys in the battle for Bihar}}</ref>\n* [[Bashistha Narain Singh]], Bihar [[JD(U)]] President, Member of Parliament in Rajya Sabha.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/patna-news/unopposed-bashishtha-narayan-singh-re-elected-jd-u-bihar-unit-president-1466277|url-status = live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406020718/http://www.ndtv.com/patna-news/unopposed-bashishtha-narayan-singh-re-elected-jd-u-bihar-unit-president-1466277|archivedate=6 April 2017|title=Unopposed, Bashishtha Narayan Singh Re-Elected JD(U) Bihar Unit President}}</ref>\n* [[Rajiv Ranjan Singh]], Minister for Water Resources, [[Government of Bihar]], Former Bihar [[JD(U)]] President.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/nitish-kumarss-team-7-masters-9-grads-and-12-who-went-to-school/|url-status = live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20151205215544/http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/nitish-kumarss-team-7-masters-9-grads-and-12-who-went-to-school/|archivedate=5 December 2015|title=Nitish Kumar's Bihar team: 7 Masters, 9 graduates and 12 who went to school|date=2015-11-22}}</ref>\n\n==List of Chief Ministers ==\n\n* [[Nitish Kumar]]:\n** First term: 3 March 2000 to 10 March 2000\n** Second term: 24 November 2005 to 26 November 2010\n** Third term: 26 November 2010 to 20 May 2014\n** Fourth term: 22 February 2015 to 20 November 2015\n** Fifth term: 20 November 2015 to 26 July 2017\n** Sixth term: 27 July 2017 to present\n* [[Jitan Ram Manjhi]] (former member):\n** First term: 20 May 2014 to 22 February 2015\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official}}\n\n{{National Democratic Alliance}}\n{{Indian poli